          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnaudioplayer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object controls playback of a positional audio source in a SceneKit scene. To use positional audio, first create a reusable "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnaudiosource"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " or "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfaudio/avaudionode"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object to provide an audio stream. Then, create an audio player to control the playback of that audio source. Finally, attach the audio player to an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnnode"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object for spatialized 3D audio playback based on the position of that node relative to the scene’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnscenerenderer/1523747-audiolistener"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " node."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
